		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Clarence Place</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>30 May /47</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p>My Dear Sir&#44;</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)">I return you many<lb/> thanks for your last kind<lb/> favor.  The bill on <date>10th</date> [&#63;]<lb/> for &#163;11..7..10&#8211;which she has<lb/> accepted.  I promised to refund<lb/> to me tomorrow&#8211;  This must<lb/> I fear be a very brief &amp; little<lb/> satisfactory epistle&#44; for I am<lb/> much hurried&#44; &amp; from long<lb/> continued indisposition correspondence<lb/> has been &amp; is a great fatigue<lb/> but I am anxious to acknowledge</p>

		<pb n="2"/>
		
			<p>your remittance  I explained<lb/> that my last work &#34;House<lb/> Influence a Sale for Mothers and daughters&#34; is <hi rend="underline">not</hi> published<lb/> at my own expense&#8211;The profits<lb/> whatever they may be are to<lb/> be divided between my<lb/> publisher &#40;who has taken the<lb/> whole risk&#41; &amp; myself&#8211;therefore<lb/> I should be glad if they book could<lb/> get a circulation in <placeName>America</placeName><lb/> but I could not send them<lb/> out.  <persName>Mrssrs Carey &amp; Hart</persName>&#44; if<lb/> they <hi rend="underline">really</hi> wish for theirs<lb/> must write themselves to<lb/> <persName>Miss Greenbridge</persName> &amp; Sons<lb/> <placeName>5 Patornostor low Cheapside<lb/> London</placeName>&#8211;&amp; their order will<lb/> of course be attended to<lb/> I will enclose with this</p>

		<pb n="3"/>
		
			<p>some notices of the<lb/> work which have been printed<lb/> on my publishers monthly<lb/> lists of <date>May</date> &amp; <date>June</date>&#44; which<lb/> will give you an idea how<lb/> favorably it has been received<lb/> by the English generally.  I<lb/> do not near[&#63;] my own people<lb/> for I would never publish<lb/> a work of general storation<lb/> depending on <hi rend="underline">their</hi> support.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">My Jewish Faith has<lb/> here received with much<lb/> encouragement by the Jews in<lb/> <placeName>England</placeName>&#8211;&amp; started[&#63;] to land<lb/> so very high as an useful<lb/> work for the proper [&#63;]<lb/> if our Holy Faith &amp; effectual<lb/> guard against the [&#63;]</p>

		<pb n="4"/>
		
			<p>Christianity&#44; that I cannot<lb/> but believe it will be received<lb/> with the same favor by my<lb/> Jewish friends in <placeName>America</placeName> You would<lb/> oblige me very much by<lb/> informing <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs Cohen</persName> of [&#63;]<lb/> of the work for I am about<lb/> starting for <placeName>Germany</placeName> next<lb/> <date>Tuesday</date> evening&#44; I cannot<lb/> spare time to write to them<lb/> myself.  We expect to be<lb/> absent from <placeName>England</placeName> till<lb/> the beginning or end of <date>September</date><lb/> consequently you will not be<lb/> surprised even if you should<lb/> have occasion to write on [&#63;]<lb/> to me&#8211;at not receiving any<lb/> communication from me till<lb/> my return.  I have nearly<lb/> forgotten to say I had <hi rend="underline">no intentions</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">whatever</hi> of having a second edition<lb/> of the &#34;[&#63;] of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#34; printed<lb/> in <placeName>America</placeName>.  I only asked the</p>

		<pb n="5"/>
		
			<p>cost from curiosity.  I could get it<lb/> reprinted for somewhat less than your<lb/> stated sum in <placeName>England</placeName>&#44; therefore should<lb/> never think of restoring or [&#63;] a<lb/> speculation in <placeName>America</placeName>.  With<lb/> many thanks for all your friendly<lb/> exertions in my favor I remain</p>
		  <p rend="indent(5)">Dear Sir</p>
		  <p rend="indent(5)">Yours truly</p>
		  <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Grace Aguilar</persName></p>
			<p>I hope your health is improving</p>
		</body>
